<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/1239930-did-anyone-else-realize-that-the-witness">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Did anyone else realize that the Witness, Ella's, storyline was the only one written from a first person perspective? (Well, with the exception of the Watcher)<br /><br />Ella used phrases like I, and my Tony, my Luke, while all the other storylines were written from the outside looking in. Henry did this, Sarah did that, Matthew thought.<br /><br />Just a little something, something, I noticed. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
