        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2135997018" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15653670703836948803">Ella Longfield becomes an unwitting sort of witness when she overhears a conversation while on the bus. Two young teenage girls start flirting with two young men .. but then she realizes that they men are fresh out of prison.<br/><br/>What to do? Call the parents of the girls? Tell the young men to leave the girls along? Talk to the girls and warn them? Just as she decides to call for help, she overhears something else that stops her in her tracks.<br/><br/>The next day one of the girl&apos;s picture is splashed all ove</span>
  <span id="freeText15653670703836948803" style="display:none">Ella Longfield becomes an unwitting sort of witness when she overhears a conversation while on the bus. Two young teenage girls start flirting with two young men .. but then she realizes that they men are fresh out of prison.<br /><br />What to do? Call the parents of the girls? Tell the young men to leave the girls along? Talk to the girls and warn them? Just as she decides to call for help, she overhears something else that stops her in her tracks.<br /><br />The next day one of the girl's picture is splashed all over the media. She disappeared the night before.<br /><br />A year later, Ella still feels guilty that she did nothing and someone else thinks she should pay, as well. She's received a series of threatening letters.<br /><br />Someone knows where Anna is—and they’re not telling. But they are watching Ella.<br /><br />I AM WATCHING YOU is told by different voices... Ella, the friend who was with the missing girl the night she disappeared and her family, and the private detective that Ella hires to track down the person sending her letters.<br /><br />These are all credible characters ... and some of them have secrets .... and some are buried in lies. Many twists and turns will have you momentarily forgetting to breathe. <br /></span>
